full_text: In this demonstration, I will show you two ways in which you can add a document. Documents can be added to accounts, policies, or jobs. I will start with the right construction account. To create or upload a document, click Action, New Document, or go to the Documents page on the left. The Upload Documents tab appears in the lower part of the screen. Select Add Files. Navigate to a file. This is an example, so I will select a text file. Click Open to choose the file. Now I will add the required details for the file. This includes the status and the document type. I am going to select the document type here. And finally, I am selecting a section type. Now I can upload this new document. Let me show you how to create a document from a template. This time I will attach the document to a policy. Click Actions, click Actions, and New Document. Then select Create from a template. To find the specific template, select Search. For this example, I will just select Other. I am specifying English as the language. From the options, I am selecting a document type related to the quote. After verifying the details, I am going to click Create Document. This creates the document from the template. When I click Update, the document gets attached to the policy. The document is not actually uploaded, but it is referred to. The document might reside on a document server. Verify the document is related to the policy by selecting Documents.
